ÈÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍÍ¼

   Here's a step-by-step quick installation of Legend of the Red Dragon:

STEP ONE:

   Uncompress the LORD.ZIP archive into a directory of your choice.

STEP TWO:

   Edit the START.BAT with your favorite text editor. Change the top line to
   reflect the directory where you uncompressed Legend of the Red Dragon into.
   It will need to change to the Legend of the Red Dragon directory before
   executing anything else in the batch file.

STEP THREE:

   Run LORDCFG.EXE.

   In LORDCFG, go to (S)etup Nodes. This will allow you to configure baud rates,
   locked baud rates, COM ports, special port addresses (if needed)m the
   dropfile type your BBS makes, and where to find it.

   If you run a multi-node BBS, set up EACH dial in/remote node.

   Lazy Folks: Every time you set up a node that does not exist in LORDCFG, the
   new node configuration will be created with the defaults of the first node
   installed. So, if you have 200 nodes, it won't be a huge pain in the ass to
   set up all 200 of them.

STEP FOUR:

   Have your BBS execute the START.BAT. If you run just one node (A single line
   BBS), you need to have your BBS call START.BAT 1. The 1 is the node number.

   If you have a multi-node BBS, use a node parameter (in RemoteAccess, it's *N)
   so your BBS will substitute the appropriate node number.

TO PLAY LOCALLY:

   If you want to just play Legend of the Red Dragon locally, just start it with
   the LOCAL.BAT file.

















