   This part is included if you are having problems with Legend of the Red
Dragon.

Q: Uh... My network is simply not letting other nodes play when someone is    
   already in the game.

A: No one has ever asked that - BUT, if it does happen, it's possible you can
   fix it by typing "ATTRIB +R START.BAT" at the DOS prompt to make the
   START.BAT read only.

   Your network could be locking it away from the other users when someone is in
   Legend of the Red Dragon.

   But, since I don't use CALL in the batch file, it should be done with it
   completely when it changed to the LSS(node number).BAT automatically. So this
   scenario may never happen.

Q: Hey! It ain't making score bulletins like it should! Instead I'm getting a
   runtime error when someone quits. How can I fix this?

A: The Fix: When you entered the path of your ASCII and ANSI files in LORDCFG,
   did you forget to enter the NAME of the score files you want created?

   GO FIX IT!

Q: The game is saying someone else is playing the game, even though that user
   isn't on. What's up?

A: This is caused by the game turning off unexpectedly. For instance, a lock up,
   or a power failure. A carrier loss will not do this, Legend of the Red Dragon
   knows how to handle that, and will save all the players data before it
   returns to the BBS.

   The game will automatically fix it at maintenance the next morning, but you
   can also use the "(T)urn "On Now" Stat off for all players" option in
   LORDCFG.

Q: When a user enters the door, nothing happens, and he is returned back to the
   BBS! How can I get around this?

A: Check your BBS's execution string. It's probably not finding the file. It
   should look something like this:

   C:\BBS\DOORS\LORD\START.BAT 1

   ** OR **

   The problem could be Legend of the Red Dragon isn't getting enough memory.
   LORD requires 350k of CONVENTIONAL memory.

   You may need to tell your BBS to Swap to Disk instead of memory to get
   enough. WWIV SysOps: Use the Shrink BBS option.





