   Here's a more detailed explanation of each Game Option:

   (D)eletion Grace Period is Currently 15 days - This option allows you to set
   the MAXIMUM number of days that a player can miss before he is deleted out of
   the game.

   (G)SZ Path and Name - This option allows you to set a path for an external
   protocol driver so that in-game downloading of LORDICONS.ZIP is possible.
   This needs to be set if you know some players will be using RIPTerm. If you
   cannot get the in-game downloading of LORDICONS.ZIP to work, add the file
   somewhere on your BBS so your users can download it from there.

   (3) Giving credit to NO ONE! for registering - You an optionally add your
   name, or if a user registered Legend of the Red Dragon, you can put his name
   here as well. Leaving it blank will just show "REGISTERED!" in the title
   screen.
   {*} Registered Only

   (4) Multinode Support - This option allows you to toggle multi-node support
   for Legend of the Red Dragon. If you run a multi-node BBS, then you would
   most likely want this option set to YES.

   (F)orest Fights Per Day - This option allows you to increase the number of
   forest fights per day that a player is allowed to have. It is recommended
   that you do not set this higher than 30. Giving a player more than 30 forest
   fights per day means that they will advance through the game rather rapidly.
   Lowering it to a number lower than 15 will make the game move real slow! 
   {*} Registered Only

   (H)uman Fights per Day - This option determines how many user battles, or
   player fights he is allowed per day. Setting this to a number greater than 3
   means that everybody in the game gets slaughtered. {* Registered Only}


