   Here's a more detailed explanation of every option:

   (1) Name - This is the players name in LORD.

   (2) Level - The players level in the game.

   (3) Real Name - The players real name as set by the BBS.

   (4) Hit Points - This is the maximum hit points a player can take before he
   is killed.

   (5) Experience - This is the amount of experience the player has in the game.

   (6) Hit Max - This is the maximum hit points a player has. The formula for
   this is: HITPOINTS / MAX HITPOINTS. I.E. If a player had 520 hit points, and
   his maximum hit points were 1000, he would have XX Max Hits.

   (7) Weapon - Allows you to change the name of the weapon the player has.

   (8) Weapon Num - Allows you to change the weapon number the player has. Here
   is a list of the weapons:

   (9) Seen Master - Toggles whether or not if the player has seen his master in
   Turgons Warrior Training.

   (0) Fights Day - Toggles how many forest fights a player has left for today.

   (A) Fights Human - Toggles how many player fights (fighting other players) a
   player has left for the day.

   (B) Sex - Player's Sex (Male/Female).

   (C) Defense - Toggles the amount of player defense the player has left.

   (D) Gems - How many gems the player has.


Legend of the Red Dragon 4.02                                  Page 21

   (E) Strength - How much attack strength a player has.

   (F) Charm - The amount of charm points a player has.

   (G) Seen Dragon - Tells whether or not if the player has done battle with the
   infamous Red Dragon yet today.

   (H) SeenVoilet - Tells whether or not if the player has flirted with Violet.

   (I) Class - The players class. Either Deathknight, Mystical, or Thieving.

   (J) Times Won - Displays how many times the player has defeated the Red
   Dragon. This will also sow up in the Hall of Fame in Turgons Warrior
   Training.

   (K) Armour - The name of the current players armour.

   (L) Armour Num - The current number of the player's armour. Here's a list of
   the valid armour numbers:

   (M) Player Dead? - Is the player dead or alive?

   (N) StayingInn - Tells whether or not if the player is staying in the Inn.

   (O) Gold - The amount of gold the player has on hand.

   (P) Seen Bard - Tells whether or not if the player has asked Seth Able the
   Bard to sing.

   (R) Gold in Bank - The amount of gold the player has in the bank.

   (S) Times Laid - Tells how many times the player has gotten laid by either
   Violet (male), Seth Able (female) or other players (total).

   (T) Player Kills - Tells how many times the player has killed other players.

   (U) Flirted Player? - Tells whether or not if the player has flirted with
   another player yet today.

   (X) Delete 'em - Deletes the current player from the game.

   (W) Search by Name - Allows you to search through all the players by a name
   or a partial name. 

   ($) Edit Skills - Toggles how many uses of each skill a player has per day.
   Either Deathknight, Mystical, or Thieving.

   (]) Advance One - Advances to the next player record.

   ([) Back Up One - Backs up to the previous player record.

   (*) New Day for User - Resents the current players stats for today. This will
   make them alive again, flirts for today will be set to No, will get their
   daily forest and player fights per day back, and will earn 10% interest of
   their total gold in the bank.

   (Q) Quit and Save - Quits and saves any changes made to the current player
   record.



